<TITLE> Two RMG workers die in road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 4 (bdnews24.com)  At least two garment workers were killed after a bus ran over them in Chittagong's Agrabad area Monday morning. Thirteen workers, who were injured in the accident, were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Doublemooring police chief Manjurul Haque said the workers of Multiplus Garments, located at Chittagong Export Processing Zone, were waiting for factory bus at Choumuhoni area at around 7:30am. The driver of the particular bus while trying to pull over to pick up the waiting workers lost control and ploughed through them leaving 15 people, most of them women, injured. Kamal Hossain, sub-inspector of CMCH police post, said Aleya Begum and Rina Akhter succumbed to injuries in the hospital. Haque said police had seized the bus, but its driver and conductor managed to flee the scene. 
